                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>&#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/>
                New York&#44; Oct 14&#34;87<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr and Dear Sir&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>I have to report<lb/> that the preparatory class of the Jewish<lb/> Theol. Seminary made very fair progress<lb/> during the month of September although<lb/> considerably interrupted by the holy days.<lb/>  The subjects taught were&#44; Pentateuch&#44; Genesis<lb/> cap. VI&#44; VII &#38; half of VIII with &#91;Hebrew&#93;&#44; Psalms XVIII to XXIII<lb/> with exegetical and <hi rend="underline">ethical</hi> explanations&#44; Grammar<lb/> irregular verbs &#91;Hebrew&#93;&#44; &#91;Hebrew&#93;&#44; &#91;Hebrew&#93; and &#91;Hebrew&#93;&#44; History&#44; the<lb/> Prophet Samuel &#38; the beginning of the Kings&#44; Talmud<lb/> one page &#91;Hebrew&#93;&#44; and Mishna &#91;Hebrew&#93; Cap II &#38; III<lb/> with Bartenora.  The boys have now a literary<lb/> and debating club which meets regularly.<lb/>  Through the efforts of Mr Blumenthal<lb/> a handsome book case and desk<lb/> have been secured and the room<lb/> presents a very neat appearance.<lb/>  I shall be obliged to give up Sebogic&#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>grammar which is at present in use<lb/> and which is very unsatisfactory.<lb/>  I have the honor to be&#44; Sir<lb/> Very truly yours<lb/> Bernard Drachman<lb/> 439 E. 56<hi rend="sup">th</hi> St<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
